\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Instructions for the Debate\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

\b0 \cf0 \
Before the Debate:  Team Partners should work with each other to determine\'97\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

\b \cf0 Affirmative
\b0 \'85what are your three arguments?  Start with well worded claims.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\ri0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 1.	Problem\
2.	Inherency\
3.	Solvency\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 \
Once you know the three claims then communicate the claims to the negative.\
You can then work together to construct the rest of your case.  You can anticipate what the negative might say to refute your arguments and then plan on what your next response might be. When the negative communicates their disadvantages to you, then you can work to prepare refutation responses and defense of the plan.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

\b \cf0 Negative
\b0 \'85what are your two disadvantages?  In particular you need to determine:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\ri0
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 1.	The main Disadvantage Claim\
2.	The claim for the link to harm\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 \
Once you know the two disadvantages, then communicate the claims to the affirmative.\
You can work together to finish constructing the disadvantages.  And when you know the three affirmative arguments you can work together to prepare some refutation arguments.  Anticipate what the affirmative will say to your arguments and prepare some briefs to extend.\
\
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

\b \cf0 Information about the debate\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

\b0 \cf0 \
Objective:  The affirmative must prove the resolution to the judges to win; otherwise the negative team will win.  You must convince a majority of the judges to win the decision.  No ties will be allowed.  In addition to win\\loss the judges will score you individually based on their perception of how well you debated in fulfilling your specific duties.\
\
Rules:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\ri0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 	All arguments have to be introduced and argued within the time allotted per speech.\
	Speakers will be stopped if they go into overtime.\
	New arguments are not allowed in rebuttals, except the 1AR is allowed to refute disadvantages even if the refutation response is new.  Extensions of arguments in constructives are allowed in refutation arguments in rebuttals and new evidence may be read in rebuttals, but only to support arguments introduced in constructives.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0

